Class AllocatedProteinEntry

java.lang.Object
datastructure.AllocatedProteinEntry
public class AllocatedProteinEntry
extends java.lang.Object
Internal object representation of a protein that was allocated to a single FeatureEntry.

  • Method Details

    • generateProteoformName

      private java.lang.String generateProteoformName​(java.lang.String vSwab)
      Returns a String that is used as internal proteoform name.

      These names are generated by concatenating the prefix 'PF' with the HashCode of the ProteoformEntry mandatory 'VSWAB' annotation value converted to a String for which a negative sign is converted to a one and which in total was padded with prepending 0s to a length of 10.

      Parameters:
      vSwab - The String value of the 'VSWAB' annotation of a ProteoformEntry.
      Returns:
      String intended to be used as internal proteoform name.

    • addProteoform

      public void addProteoform​(FeatureEntry fEntry, java.lang.String sId, java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentSkipListMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> variants)
      Adds a new ProteoformEntry to the proteoforms structure.
      Parameters:
      fEntry - The FeatureEntry to whose FeatureEntry.allocatedProtein the entry shall be added.
      sId - The String sample identifier of any SampleEntry of which the proteoform was derived.
      variants - ConcurrentSkipListMap of Strings that maps positions wrt. the reference wild-type proteoform to alternate amino-acid contents.
